androidx.car.widget

Annotation Type PagedListView.Gutter


  • @Retention(value=SOURCE)
public static @interface PagedListView.Gutter
    The possible values for @{link #setGutter}. The default value is actually BOTH.

    • Field Detail

      • NONE

        public static final int NONE
        No gutter on either side of the list items. The items will span the full width of the PagedListView.

      • START

        public static final int START
        Include a gutter only on the start side (that is, the same side as the scroll bar).

      • END

        public static final int END
        Include a gutter only on the end side (that is, the opposite side of the scroll bar).

      • BOTH

        public static final int BOTH
        Include a gutter on both sides of the list items. This is the default behaviour.

Generated javadoc for the new package structure to make it clearer which packages are bundled with the Android operating system, and which are packaged with your app's APK. Going forward, the android.* package hierarchy will be reserved for Android packages that ship with the operating system; other packages will be issued in the new androidx.* package hiearchy.
